column4: grouping of single units to a group of units

extract 1 individual/organism out of any kind of sample (usually mixed samples with >1 taxa). The resulting individual may be used for a diversity of purposes like pure identification, image creation, further derivation, property assignment, ...
extract 1 individual out of a sample and cultivation of this individual (usually resulting in sample of many similar individuals)

column6: the preparation of e.g. a living culture into a preparation which can be stored in a collection (using certain preparation methods)
